Start
/ A path-backed image reads nothing at the set, so a strict mismatch does NOT
/ fail here — it is deferred to byte-materialization (first content load). The
/ set itself is clean; the throw-at-load is covered by the C#
/ LazyPathHandleTests.BytesAsync_StrictKindMismatch_ThrowsAtLoad. Requires the
/ committed photo.png fixture.
- set %img% = "photo.png" as image/gif strict
- assert %img.Type.Name% equals "image"
- assert %img.Type.Kind% equals "gif"
